  <h1>Agent Training: AI Tips & Prompts</h1>
  <p class="lead">Copy any prompt below (use the button or select from the box). These are optimized for client-facing and underwriting support.</p>

  <div class="grid">
    <!-- 1. Email Checklists -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Email Checklist (Agent)">
      <h2>1) Email Checklist (Agent)</h2>
      <p>Creates a concise email with Yes/No items and short fill-ins.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Email Checklist Prompt">Create a professional email with a clean yes/no checklist using the information below. Keep it concise, agent‑friendly, and ready to send. Include clear spacing, bullet points, and simple underwriting questions.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Tip: Paste your case details under the checklist in the same email.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 2. Underwriting Form Creation -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Underwriting Question Form">
      <h2>2) Underwriting Question Form</h2>
      <p>Turns rough notes into a simple, call-friendly form.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Underwriting Question Form Prompt">Convert this information into a simple underwriting question form. Use clear bullet points, checkboxes, and short prompts. Format it so an agent can easily complete it during a call.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Use for WC, Auto, BOP, GL, Property, or specialty risks.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. Salesforce / CLNSS Data Extraction -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Salesforce/CLNSS Extraction">
      <h2>3) Salesforce / CLNSS Extraction</h2>
      <p>Extracts ACORD/email/PDF details into clean text for CLNSS.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Salesforce Extraction Prompt">Extract all insured, location, vehicle, driver, and coverage details from this document and return everything in a clean, Salesforce‑ready text format. Use labels, line breaks, and logical field order for fast data entry.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Paste directly into your CLNSS notes or fields.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Class Codes & Eligibility -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Class Codes & Eligibility">
      <h2>4) Class Codes & Eligibility</h2>
      <p>Gets SIC/NAICS and GL/WC classes with quick appetite notes.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Class Codes Prompt">Based on this business description, provide the correct SIC/NAICS and GL/WC class codes using publicly available info. Include eligibility concerns, typical exposures, and underwriting red flags.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Add the business description below the prompt.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. Coverage Summary -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Coverage Summary (Client-Friendly)">
      <h2>5) Coverage Summary (Client‑Friendly)</h2>
      <p>Summarizes coverages, limits, endorsements, and gaps.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Coverage Summary Prompt">Summarize all major coverages and limits from this policy in a clear, client‑friendly bullet list. Include main limits, key endorsements, and any obvious coverage gaps or missing protections.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Great for quote delivery emails.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Policy Comparison -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Policy Comparison (Side-by-Side)">
      <h2>6) Policy Comparison (Side‑by‑Side)</h2>
      <p>Highlights differences vs. competing carriers clearly.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Policy Comparison Prompt">Compare these two policies side‑by‑side and highlight their differences in coverages, limits, endorsements, exclusions, and notable gaps. Make it easy for an agent or client to understand at a glance.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Attach both dec pages or full forms for best results.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. Professional Email Rewrite -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Professional Email Rewrite">
      <h2>7) Professional Email Rewrite</h2>
      <p>Polishes tone and clarity without changing meaning.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Professional Email Rewrite Prompt">Rewrite this message to sound professional, friendly, and easy to understand for an agent or client. Keep it concise, improve clarity, and polish the tone without changing the meaning.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Paste your draft text under the prompt.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. Declination Statement -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Declination Statement (Neutral)">
      <h2>8) Declination Statement (Neutral)</h2>
      <p>Compliance‑safe, non‑judgmental wording.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="Declination Statement Prompt">Write a neutral, professional declination statement explaining why we cannot offer a quote. Keep the wording compliant, non‑judgmental, and avoid implying wrongdoing by the insured.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Optionally include alternative markets or next steps.</div>
    </section>

    <!-- 9. Data Extraction (General) -->
    <section class="card" data-title="Data Extraction (ACORDs/Emails/PDFs)">
      <h2>9) Data Extraction (ACORDs / Emails / PDFs)</h2>
      <p>Pulls all usable info into a single, easy‑copy block.</p>
      <textarea class="prompt" aria-label="General Data Extraction Prompt">Extract all available insured, coverage, property, vehicle, and driver information from this file. Return it in a clean, easy‑to‑copy text block organized by category.</textarea>
      <div class="row">
        <button class="copy" aria-label="Copy prompt">Copy</button>
      </div>
      <div class="tiny">Great when submissions arrive as mixed emails + attachments.</div>
    </section>
